<br>
A single group can get HoH access..<br>
Get a group together sometime and do the PoN caves for the memphit. Heck, most people won't even know what the drop is for when it drops, and some people won't care once you tell them.  Get a partner and do the PoJ crap, get a 3 man group and go to PoI and get that peice. While time consuming, if you're with people while you do this, it meets your goal of meeting new people. I don't know many people that wouldn't want to group with a 65 mage in PoI or PoN. Both zones have active groups, and PoN has many people which would, I'm sure, want to do caves as it's very nice xp. The Quest itself is a 6 person encounter.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub146.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showMessage?topicID=5930.topic" target="top">HoH quest</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
Get CoD access: FInd a tracker and go to Plane of disease. The mobs that drop the CoD access are fairly easy, and you might be able to solo it even at 65. Again, it's a 6man encounter (or less)<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub146.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showMessage?topicID=5747.topic">CoD Quest</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
Get BoT access: Remenber back in the day when people held naggy/vox raids? Why not do the same for the named in PoS. Reserve one of the 3 that drop for you and random the other 2, or random all 3, would be your call on that. I'm sure, just by reading this board, that there are many others that would love to help and join in on this. The PoS named are 9man doable with &quot;uber&quot; equipment, so gather 20-30 people and it shouldn't be too hard. To people that complain the chance of them getting loot is slim, so were the drops off naggy/vox. 3-4 things dropped off them at a time max and you had 40-50 people on the raid..the chances were even slimmer back then but they managed to get people quite a few times to kill them. Also, if you catch them at the right time you can kill more than one named, bringing the chances for a medalion MUCH more.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/quest.html?quest=2269">BoT Quest</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
PoI dragon: While not easy, it can be done with the same strategy as above. Whats' more is everyone involved with the killing of it, gets access to the factory floor in PoI, not just 3. There are trial-like things inside the floor that could be fun for you (6 person encounters) and the mobs inside of it are semi good xp also.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/quest.html?quest=2207">Factory floor quest info</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
Also, while maybe not useful, PoNb is doable with pickup's. I have friends in guilds not able to kill vindi, that have access to PoNb so it's not too hard. They're also only lvl 62-63 at most. It's doable, just need to find the people. That's the hard part with doing it unguilded.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/quest.html?quest=2219">PoNb Quest </a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
Don't flame, lol. I'm not trying to mock you, or anyone. I'm trying to help come up with ideas to help you get along further in the game. I understand some of the methods above would require alot of hard work, but you need to ask yourself, is it worth it? Do you &quot;really&quot; want to advance in PoP, or are you just plain getting tired of the game and trying to find excuses for it. I myself fall into that second category. The only difference is now that I am advanced, I still find myself bored with the game, and logging on less than I used to. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.power3d.com/Arch/member_inv.asp?member_id=263">Hobie Wan</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
65th level slacker mage<br>
