<br>
So should a player be penalyzed because he doesn't want co-workers, just about 5 friends to run around killing stuff with?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
I don't consider my guildmates co-workers.  They're friends.  We've gamed an awful lot together and had plenty of interesting discussions on our guild board.  I chose my guild because I like the people in it and we share a common view towards the game.  Our guild motto is RL &gt; EQ.  An obnoxious uberguild is not going to have such a motto.<br>
<br>
You say a player shouldn't be penalized for only wanting to play with five other people.  One could also say a player shouldn't be penalized for wanting to solo through the entire game.  The game is designed for social interaction on a large scale.  If you don't get involved with large groups of people you're going to miss out on significant parts of the game.<br>
<br>
Also, when I said totally independent player, I did not mean someone who only plays solo.  I meant someone who relies on his /friends list.<br>
<br>
Hey, play the game however you want.  It's just that refusing to get involved with a guild seems silly to me, given the nature of the game.  There are many different kinds of guilds out there.  You can even start one of your own by drafting nine people off your friends list. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=363562" target="top">Shazar Oom</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->62 Arch Mage<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.eqheroes.com" target="top">Heroes</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> of Luclin<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><br>
